    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Aaaah:( I hate to make things complicated here, but I believe we can't introduce this feature without a change to dapp permission dialogs, at minimum. \r\n\r\n'Who you have added as a contact' could be privacy sensitive information. As a user and as Status I would want to know how the DApp handles this information. @simonricoo @errorists can you sync on what changes the permission dialog would need without investing too much effort for the time being?\r\n\r\nIn the meantime I think we should hash out the privacy impact in this thread so we can decide:\r\n\r\n- do we allow for a getContacts function at all\r\n- what might be done with this function (minimal threat modeling)\r\n- If we allow getContacts function what should be communicated to the user allowing the sharing of contacts\r\n- If we allow getContacts function what should be communicated to the user sharing their Whisper ID/Contact key to anyone else (as it might be exposed by the individuals with initial access)\r\n- how might this feature be impacted when multiple chat keys are used\r\n",
